swatch: swatch (Simple WATCHdog)
swatch:
swatch: Swatch was originally written to actively monitor messages as they
swatch: are written to a log file via the UNIX syslog utility.  For a
swatch: simple demonstration type "perl swatch --examine=FILENAME" with
swatch: FILENAME being the file that you would like to see the contents
swatch: of. All this example will do is demonstrate the different text
swatch: modes that are available with to the echo action.
swatch:
